ce:section.ce:para:
To investigate the sensitivity for detection of tutin, the fluorescence intensity of Tyr-Cu NCs in the presence of rutin were monitored at excitation of 435 nm (the final amounts of rutin were 0, 0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 0.7, 0.9, 1, 3, 5, 10, 15, 20, 30, 40, 50, 60, 70, 80 and 90 μM). With the increase of rutin concentration, the fluorescence intensity at 480 nm was gradually decreased (Fig. 6
                        A). An excellent linear relationship was discovered between the relative fluorescence intensity (F0/F) and the amounts of rutin in the range of 0.1–1 μM (Fig. 6B) and 1–60 μM (Fig. 6C). The linear fitting equations of the detection system were F0/F = 0.038[Rutin]+0.9999 (R2 = 0.9950) (0.1−1 μM) and F0/F = 0.022[Rutin]+0.9865 (R2 = 0.9928) (1−60 μM). The corresponding detection limit (LOD) was 0.016 μM (S/N = 3), which was significantly better than other methods (Table 1
                        ).
